com.github.tommyettinger.ds

Interface Ordered<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Arrangeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    OrderedMap, OrderedSet

    public interface Ordered<T>
extends Arrangeable
    Ensures that implementors allow access to the order of T items as an ArrayList. This is meant to allow different (typically insertion-ordered) data structures to all have their order manipulated by the same methods. This interface extends Arrangeable, which itself is compatible both with primitive-backed collections like IntList and generic ones like the implementations of Ordered. This has default implementations of Arrangeable.swap(int, int) and Arrangeable.shuffle(Random).
